1. First I have created a AWS sandbox in the cloudguru website
2. created a EC2 instance for terraform in us-east-1 region
3. installed terraform and git in the ec2 instance.
4. created a vpc and ec2 directory for writing terraform code
5. In vpc directory i have created all the code related to provisioning VPC, private & public subnets, Internet gateways, Security Groups, routes, and all the code related 
to on how to connect internet gateways, subnets, VPC.
6. In EC2 directory i have executed all the code related nginx ec2 server creation
7. Now after Nginx server installation, went inside the server and installed nginx server and created a sample webpage.
8. now pushed all the above mentioned data into public repository.
